track.name: Howlin' for My Baby
comments: Not my favorite Wolf cut, but ANY Wolf is good.
Bet his baby knows it's her man howlin'.  Nobody howls like the Wolf!
play it Howlin, proper version this one.
what the fuck is this, you cant sing it with a pussy voice like that

Not the best cut. It's a bit too smooth for my taste. I love Howlin Wolf though.


Aaaawooooooooh
She's hot like red pepper. Sweet like cherry wine...

Thanks to the British Boys for given credit to the True Blues Men. Howlin' Wolf was one of the very Best of his Generation. I do remember how their sounds could be heard in any Black neighborhood during the 1950's. I still have to return to their sounds for clarification and a sense of soul.
howlin' wolf. what a man. my music ain't as good, but similar generation an' all. have a listen! http://www.last.fm/music/B.C.+Williamson
